OL,3,CAssisted dying: Will potential law in
OL,4,CJersey catalyse nationwide change?
OL,6,FWhat is assisted dying?
OL,8,FAssisted dying refers to the practice
OL,9,Fwhere a person, typically someone
OL,10,Fterminally ill, seeks assistance to
OL,11,Fend their own life.
OL,13,FThere are two main forms of assisted
OL,14,Fdying: euthanasia, where a medical
OL,15,Fprofessional administers a lethal dose
OL,16,Fof medication to the patient, or
OL,17,Fphysician-assisted suicide, when a
OL,18,Fmedical professional provides the
OL,19,Fmeans for the patient to self-
OL,20,Fadminister.
