OL,3,CAssisted dying: Will potential law in
OL,4,CJersey catalyse nationwide change?
OL,6,FOver 6,000 respondents voted 47% in
OL,7,Ffavour of opposing a change in the law
OL,8,Fon assisted dying, for reasons such as
OL,9,Ffears of putting vulnerable patients
OL,10,Fat risk, moral objections and
OL,11,Freligious beliefs.
OL,13,FMeanwhile, 40% voted to support a
OL,14,Fchange in the law on assisted dying,
OL,15,Fproviding there is a regulatory
OL,16,Fframework and appropriate safeguarding
OL,17,Fprocesses in place
OL,19,FThe RCGP told ITV News that its
OL,20,Fposition will not be reconsidered
OL,21,Funtil 2025.
