OL,6,FFollowing the committee stage, the
OL,7,Fbill returns for a second reading,
OL,8,Fwhere MPs or Lords debate the
OL,9,Flegislation.
OL,11,FIt would then receive a third reading,
OL,12,Fwhere the final version of the bill
OL,13,Fwould be debated and voted on.
OL,15,FIf the bill passes one house, it
OL,16,Fproceeds to the other house and
OL,17,Fundergoes a similar process.
OL,19,FRoyal Assent would then need to be
OL,20,Fgranted.
